r-organizational conflicts complicate the lives of the young people that they are supposed to help. Nichols’s book is essential reading for those involved in education, social services, mental health, and the justice system, as well as anyone with an interest in social justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEthnologyxMethodologyxOntarioxOntario. 0aEthnologyxResearchxOntario. 0aEthnologyxResearchzOntario. 0aEthnologyzOntarioxMethodology. 0aHomeless youthxOntario. 0aHomeless youthxServices forxOntario. 0aHomeless youthxServices forzOntario. 0aHomeless youthzOntario. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266817140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442668171423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442668171.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles